{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-jsx","path":"/blog/20210128-vertical-lines-between-tiles/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Artem Demo, indie developer","author":"Artem Demo"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"7a82ad50-0a72-50ea-92eb-44c4ff114b70","excerpt":"If you used tiles in your game, you know what I’m talking about. Usually its white lines, but they can be of any color, and it can drive you…","html":"<p>If you used tiles in your game, you know what I’m talking about.</p>\n<p>Usually its white lines, but they can be of any color, and it can drive you crazy.\nIt looks like that the problem is related to how unity allocates tiles from your sprites.\nWhile the camera moves in a scene the game engine rerender the scene and from time to time it doesn’t draw exactly the tile at exactly the place.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 381px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a7c0af56001c836053c922c56bbfe683/d3de2/vertical-line-between-tiles.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 64.86486486486486%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Vertical line between tiles\"\n        title=\"Vertical line between tiles\"\n        src=\"/static/a7c0af56001c836053c922c56bbfe683/d3de2/vertical-line-between-tiles.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a7c0af56001c836053c922c56bbfe683/3c361/vertical-line-between-tiles.png 148w,\n/static/a7c0af56001c836053c922c56bbfe683/03654/vertical-line-between-tiles.png 295w,\n/static/a7c0af56001c836053c922c56bbfe683/d3de2/vertical-line-between-tiles.png 381w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 381px) 100vw, 381px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>IMO it’s the result of optimizations on the unity side, but nevertheless we need a way to solve it.\nI found two solutions: time-consuming one and optimal one.</p>\n<p><strong>Option 1: Enlarge sprite tiles</strong></p>\n<p>The time-consuming solution is to enlarge all your tiles by one pixel and slice them one pixel less.\nHere is explanation on how to do it <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QW53YIjhQsA\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QW53YIjhQsA</a></p>\n<p>There is also free unity plugin for exactly that: <a href=\"https://assetstore.unity.com/packages/2d/textures-materials/tiles/2d-tile-gap-fixing-tool-157060\">2D Tile Gap Fixing Tool</a></p>\n<p>The second option is way simpler.</p>\n<p><strong>Option 2: Use Sprite Atlas</strong></p>\n<p>Second option will be to use Sprite Atlas. Just add it to your assets and drop in it your tileset.\nHere is nice explanation of how to do it <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Wf98KrAyB2I\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Wf98KrAyB2I</a></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 380px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d43b3a143169564332cb0c17f5dcac1a/db08c/sprite-atlas.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 145.27027027027026%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Sprite Atlas\"\n        title=\"Sprite Atlas\"\n        src=\"/static/d43b3a143169564332cb0c17f5dcac1a/db08c/sprite-atlas.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d43b3a143169564332cb0c17f5dcac1a/3c361/sprite-atlas.png 148w,\n/static/d43b3a143169564332cb0c17f5dcac1a/03654/sprite-atlas.png 295w,\n/static/d43b3a143169564332cb0c17f5dcac1a/db08c/sprite-atlas.png 380w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 380px) 100vw, 380px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>This is it.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Vertical lines between tiles in tile map in unity","date":"January 28, 2021","tags":["unity","tiles"]}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/20210128-vertical-lines-between-tiles/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/20210118-unity-object-moves-too-fast-for-the-collider-to-catch/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Object moves too fast for the collider to catch (solution for unity)","tags":["game","unity"]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/20210130-designing-games-book/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Designing Games, book by Tynan Sylvester","tags":["book","studying","game"]}}}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}